{"id": 232153950, "title": "Sri Lanka elected to the United Nations Economic and Social Council", "text": "Sri Lanka has been elected by the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) to the United Nations Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC) at the elections held in New York, on 07 June 2024, for a three-year term commencing on 01 January 2025,stated the Foreign Affairs Minister Ali Sabry. Sri Lanka obtained 182 votes, of the 189 member states present and voting, securing the 2nd highest vote count from the region, and the 7th highest number overall. Sri Lanka was previously elected to the ECOSOC from 1985 \u2013 1989 and from 2006 \u2013 2008. \u201cAs a member of the ECOSOC, Sri Lanka will contribute to the Council\u2019s efforts and programmes, which include eradication of poverty, food security, financing for development, reform of the international financial architecture to better support vulnerable countries, climate justice, gender equality and women\u2019s empowerment, rights of persons with disabilities, science and technology, and bridging the digital divide,\u201d the Foreign Affairs Ministry said in a media release.", "summary": "<div class=\"K2FeedImage\"><img src=\"https://www.news.lk/media/k2/items/cache/b6e94d42ab7f5c7d76b63fe78a799be6_S.jpg\" alt=\"Sri Lanka elected to the United Nations Economic and Social Council\" /></div><div class=\"K2FeedIntroText\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sri Lanka has been elected by the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) to the United Nations Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC) at the elections held in New York, on 07 June 2024, for a three-year term commencing on 01 January 2025,stated the Foreign Affairs Minister Ali Sabry.</p> </div>", "url": "https://www.news.lk/news/political-current-affairs/item/36474-sri-lanka-elected-to-the-united-nations-economic-and-social-council", "image": "https://www.news.lk/media/k2/items/cache/b6e94d42ab7f5c7d76b63fe78a799be6_XL.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:08:52", "author": "Pravbashini Deshabandu", "authors": ["Pravbashini Deshabandu"], "language": "en", "source_country": "lk", "sentiment": 0.511}